        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury allow the engine to cool sufficiently before performing this Service
                        Procedure.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>Refer to Figure 1</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tension from the fan belt.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove
                    <emph type="bold">one</emph>
                    hub mounting bolt and replace with the equivalent bolt from the kit. Turn the bolt until the bolt
                    flange is in contact with the hub flange.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat the procedure for the three remaining bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the fan hub mounting bolts to 80 to 100 Lbf-ft (108 to 136 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the fan belt.</para>
            </step1>
